reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A Healthier Way to Sort of Get That Deep Fried Taste
reviews.reviewText: It's been a couple of months since I bought my Cosori air fryer. I did a couple months of research before buying this model, after purchasing a full sized Cosori convection oven for my daughter's family as a house-warming gift. They really Love their family size Cosori, and I'm rather happy with my own smaller unit as well. I only use it every couple of weeks, since I eat pretty healthy, and still prefer to do my meat and veggies on a gas grill. Originally I bought this because I Love fried fish (I think fish ALWAYS tastes best when it's deep fried). I also wanted to try making healthier egg rolls and wontons. I have to say that the egg rolls and wontons turn out quite well, without having all the grease of deep frying and the cleanup and disposal issues related to deep frying. I'm still playing around with temps and times, but I am impressed with how the food turns out. Things cook much quicker in a convection oven than they do in a regular one, and the smaller size of my Cosori unit means I don't have to heat up my kitchen oven just to cook for one person. The controls are easy to use, and I really like the 'halfway timer' that lets me know when to flip my food. Overall, I think the design of the unit is quite well thought out. I love the link to online recipes and the fact that my phone keeps track of my cooking. Very, very handy! Compared to cooking on a gas grill, I still like the gas grill for roasting vegetables better than using the convection oven. Like others have said, the food still doesn't taste like deep fried - but it is certainly a healthier option that gives you a crispy outer layer while cooking the inside to perfection. I'm still playing around with air frying breaded fish fillets. I haven't perfected that yet. The conventional oven still gives me better results, but I think it's just a matter of time before I hit on the right time/temp/methods to use in my Cosori. I am very pleased with this unit and would highly recommend the Cosori brand. I included two pics of egg rolls I made, and was very happy with the results. I just may have to do some air frying tonight!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 9, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Despite a previous review from someone, this fryer will most definitely fry without a preheat if you so desire. It is the perfect size for mid-quantity meals, meaning quick and uniform heating. Much bigger than pull-out fryers but not so big as "ovens" that take so long to heat and produce uneven results.AND since this fryer will go to 450 degrees - 50 degrees higher than many fryers - you can set it at 415 and crisp up leftovers or reheat leftovers to the perfect consistency and taste.This baloney that it is hard to learn the controls - not true at all. Very easy. In fact, I prefer these controls over any other fryer I have had. This Cosori fryer is exceptionally nice in all aspects. I hope it lasts longer than 2 years. We will see. But I highly recommend this one!
